diff:1120517892:1120517399:=1,15c1,7%0a%3c !! Character and Character Creation%0a%3c %0a%3c In Fudge, characters are described using traits. Traits include Attributes, Skills, Gifts, and Faults.%0a%3c %0a%3c !!! Attributes%0a%3c %0a%3c Attributes in Fudge are characteristics common to all player and non-player characters. They are not linked to skills, so it is possible to have different categories of attributes.%0a%3c %0a%3c '''Attributeless''' characters do not list any attributes at all. The assumption is that characters are so normal that to list distinct attributes is not necessary. Rather, attributes that stand out are of such significance that they are really Gifts or Faults.%0a%3c %0a%3c '''BroadAttributes''' allow a game to progress quickly without a lot of bookkeeping. Characters only have the Body and Mind which helps describe the character and how well he deals with some situations. The Body is used whenever an action roll is needed dealing with the character's physical body.%0a%3c %0a%3c '''[[FudgeRules/SpecificAttributes]]''' are for games that want to be more accurate and more like a simulation.%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a---%0a> !! Attributes%0a> [[FudgeRules/Attributeless]]%0a> [[FudgeRules/BroadAttributes]]%0a> [[FudgeRules/SpecificAttributes]]%0a> %0a> [[FudgeRules/WealthAsAnAttribute]]%0a> %0a
